<subSubSection pageId="19" pageNumber="18" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="19.[192,1441,387,635]" pageId="19" pageNumber="18">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[192,309,387,411]" pageId="19" pageNumber="18">Remark.</emphasis>
All identified specimens of this species I observed in collections (except for the 
<typeStatus box="[1256,1367,387,411]" pageId="19" pageNumber="18">lectotype</typeStatus>
) were misidentified 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Smith" authorityYear="2008" box="[357,650,419,443]" class="Insecta" family="Melolonthidae" genus="Pusiodactylus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="19" pageNumber="18" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="mondacai">
<emphasis box="[357,650,419,443]" italics="true" pageId="19" pageNumber="18">Pusiodactylus mondacai</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. Contrary to the locality of 
<collectingRegion box="[972,1094,419,443]" country="Chile" name="Coquimbo" pageId="19" pageNumber="18">Coquimbo</collectingRegion>
given in the original description (
<bibRefCitation author="Solier, A. J. J." box="[253,390,451,475]" pageId="19" pageNumber="18" pagination="5 - 285" refId="ref19247" refString="Solier, A. J. J. 1851. Orden III. Coleopteros, pp. 5 - 285. In: C. Gay (ed.). Historia Fisica y Politica de Chile. Zoologia. Vol. 5. C. Gay; Paris. 564 p." type="book chapter" year="1851">Solier 1851</bibRefCitation>
), this species is not known from IV 
<collectingRegion box="[804,1051,451,475]" country="Chile" name="Coquimbo" pageId="19" pageNumber="18">Región de Coquimbo</collectingRegion>
, 
<collectingCountry box="[1060,1128,451,475]" name="Chile" pageId="19" pageNumber="18">Chile</collectingCountry>
. The label on the 
<typeStatus box="[1332,1441,451,475]" pageId="19" pageNumber="18">lectotype</typeStatus>
is somewhat illegible but seems to say “Copioyio” not 
<collectingRegion box="[852,981,483,507]" country="Chile" name="Coquimbo" pageId="19" pageNumber="18">Coquimbo</collectingRegion>
. Many of the localities cited by 
<bibRefCitation author="Solier, A. J. J." pageId="19" pageNumber="18" pagination="5 - 285" refId="ref19247" refString="Solier, A. J. J. 1851. Orden III. Coleopteros, pp. 5 - 285. In: C. Gay (ed.). Historia Fisica y Politica de Chile. Zoologia. Vol. 5. C. Gay; Paris. 564 p." type="book chapter" year="1851">Solier (1851)</bibRefCitation>
were erroneous and this appears to be another example.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="19.[192,1441,387,635]" pageId="19" pageNumber="18">
<bibRefCitation author="Cisternas, E. &amp; R. Carrillo" box="[240,610,547,571]" pageId="19" pageNumber="18" pagination="61 - 63" refId="ref17982" refString="Cisternas, E. and R. Carrillo. 1989. Ciclo estacional de Schizochelus serratus Phil. (Coleoptera: Scarabaeidae). Revista Chilena de Entomologia 17: 61 - 63." type="journal article" year="1989">Cisternas and Carrillo (1989)</bibRefCitation>
discussed the univoltine life cycle of this species under the name 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Philippi" authorityYear="1864" box="[192,452,579,603]" class="Insecta" family="Melolonthidae" genus="Schizochelus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="19" pageNumber="18" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="serratus">
<emphasis box="[192,452,579,603]" italics="true" pageId="19" pageNumber="18">Schizochelus serratus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. I was able to confirm the identification of their species as 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Solier" baseAuthorityYear="1851" box="[1144,1440,579,603]" class="Insecta" family="Melolonthidae" genus="Pristerophora" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="19" pageNumber="18" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="picipennis">
<emphasis box="[1144,1440,579,603]" italics="true" pageId="19" pageNumber="18">Pristerophora picipennis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
using voucher specimens from MNNC.
</paragraph>
